text: Momar Ramon N'Diaye (born 13 July 1987) is a Senegalese professional footballer who plays for FC Rodange 91. ==Career== Born in Yeumbeul, N'Diaye began his career with Génération Foot. He joined FC Metz in 2001. He played on loan for Châteauroux in the 2008–09 season. On 21 January 2010, he left Metz to sign for Rot Weiss Ahlen. After a half year and the relegation of Rot Weiss Ahlen, he left the club on 27 May 2010 to sign for FSV Frankfurt. Ahead of the 2019–20 season, N'Diaye joined FC Rodange 91.N'Diaye geht nach Rodange, pressreader.com, 12 June 2019 ==International career== N'Diaye made his debut for the Senegal national football team 2005 with only 18 years. ==Personal life== His cousins are Ibrahima Gueye and Babacar Gueye, who also played for Metz. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:Senegalese footballers Category:FC Metz players Category:LB Châteauroux players Category:Rot Weiss Ahlen players Category:FSV Frankfurt players Category:Beijing BSU F.C. players Category:China League One players Category:Ligue 1 players Category:Ligue 2 players Category:2.
